# Per-agent scripts directory.
#
# Drop ad-hoc scripts (Python or bash) the agent calls during its run.
# Each script gets the framework's standard env vars: AGENT_ID, AGENT_RUN_ID,
# AI_PROVIDER (when invoked via the API), and inherits the agent's PATH.
#
# Convention: one script per file, kebab-case names. Scripts can be
# invoked directly from the agent's run() with subprocess, OR triggered
# from the dashboard via:
#   POST /api/agents/<id>/scripts/<script-name>
#
# Useful for:
#   - One-off diagnostics ("re-fetch the GSC data, but only for this site")
#   - Per-rec implementation steps
#   - Manual operations the user wants to expose to the dashboard
